column5: Fished a little Salmon Tourney out of Port Weller on Saturday about 25 boats i believe.  It was a tough fish that day, we hooked and boat only one fish.  Popped the cherry on my wire dipsey though
nice shaker there Goran LOL, you beat me though , I am still waiting for my new wire setup to fire, was nice seeing ya there
Way to go UB, nice looking fish and glad you managed to get the new set up to fire...  Sherriff
Great stuff Goran ! Fresh air and fishin....sure beats rubber mat and metal chips fallin at your feet!
Ok, who let you hold their fish?  J/K Glad to see you got a fish on the wire rod! Awesome strikes on that set-up eh?  Tony
Goran!!!!!! Where's your PFD??????????????????????????????????????????????????????????? (see Whopper's thread!)   Nice fish buddy!

See that round ring around my stomach, oh wait that's something else...  my float suit was in the bow,not that i would have had time to put it on god forbid something happened..  I'm terrible for the lifejacket thing though... think i've only worn it 3 times, i'm better with the float suit though...  this time i brought it, i just didn't wear it, every other time, i would have worn it...  Mark, the problem with being so big, is every fish i hold, looks small...  Wayne, i've been promoted, now it's EDM & CNC and i haven't gotten a burning chip in the neck, i can't remember when... God i love the enclosure
Way to go goran....nice fish you got there..  ..i cant wait to get out there....thanks for sharing your report & pics....cheers
